    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-10-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-10-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="466"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d466">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Perry</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward.</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 5.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>, <hi
                                rend="italic">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-10-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 19, 1867.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to enclose part of the official
                    gazette of to-day, containing a royal decree, by which the present duties paid
                    in Spain and her adjacent islands upon the importation of agricultural tools and
                    machinery of all descriptions are reduced to one per cent, <hi rend="italic">ad
                        valorem,</hi> when they are brought in Spanish ships, and one-fifth part
                    more if they are imported under a foreign flag.</p>
                <p>American agricultural implements, I am glad to say, are gradually but steadily
                    being introduced, to the great benefit of the husbandry of this country, and
                    today’s decree will no doubt stimulate that trade.</p>
                <p>With sentiments of the highest respect, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HORATIO J. PERRY.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary
                            of State, Washington, D. C.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>Royal Decree.</head>
                    <p>In view of the reasons suggested by the minister of finance, in accordance
                        with the advice of the council of ministers, I decree as follows :</p>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Single article.</hi> Machinery, iron work, apparatus
                        and mechanism of foreign construction destined for agricultural uses, or
                        such as may serve for distributing the benefits and improving the products
                        of husbandry, shall pay one per cent, on their value under the national
                        flag, and one-fifth additional under a foreign flag.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <dateline rendition="#left">Done at the palace <date calendar="gregorian"
                                when="1867-10-18">the 18th day of October, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                        <lb/> Under the royal rubric.<lb/>
                        <signed>MANUEL GARCIA BARZANALLANA, <hi rend="italic">Minister of
                                Finance</hi>.</signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
